HEADWORD: Short-lived
<hw>Short"-lived`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Not living or
lasting long; being of short continuance; <as>as, a <ex>short-lived</ex>
race of beings; <ex>short-lived</ex> pleasure; <ex>short-lived</ex>
passion</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

